doc.after: The chart uses symbols to provide pilotage information about the nature and position of features useful to navigators such as sea bed information sea marks and landmarks Some symbols describe the sea bed with information such as its depth materials as well as possible hazards such as shipwrecks Other symbols show the position and characteristics of buoys lights lighthouses coastal and land features and structures that are useful for position fixing The abbreviation ED is commonly used to label geographic locations whose existence is doubtful
